Brazilian President Dilma Rousseff
today pledged 50 billion reais ($22.5 billion) for urban
mobility and public transport upgrades as policy makers seek to
quell three weeks of street protests.  Rousseff said she will create a national council to improve
public transportation, according to a post on the official
presidential blog. The president spoke today as she met with
governors and mayors in Brasilia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Malinowski in Brasilia at 
 mmalinowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
